. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1184,1211]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[314,399,1184,1210]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1037,1062]" captionTargetBox="[204,1383,166,1017]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[204,1383,166,1017]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 30. Records of Isosticta robustior." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3342301/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
). Endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[556,733,1184,1211]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
. This large species is recorded from more than 40 localities in the mountains of Grande Terre. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kimmins, D." box="[510,696,1220,1247]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="237 - 250" refId="ref33442" refString="Kimmins, D. (1958) Miss L. E. Cheesman's expedition to New Hebrides, 1955. Orders Odonata, Ephemeroptera, Neuroptera and Trichoptera. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Entomology Series, 6, 237 - 250." type="journal article" year="1958">Kimmins (1958)</bibRefCitation>
recorded it from Lifou but this island has no rivers so individuals must have dispersed from Grande Terre.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
